  "articleSummary": "The article presents a tutorial-style guide for creating Bash scripts to automate Linux server benchmarking, focusing on CPU and HDD performance using tools like `sysbench`, `inxi`, and `iotop`. It emphasizes simplifying complex benchmarking workflows by encapsulating commands into reusable functions (e.g., `benchCpu`, `benchDisk`) and ensuring dependency installation on Debian/Ubuntu systems. Key features include dynamic resource checks (e.g., CPU core counts) and structured logging of results. Targeted at system administrators and DevOps engineers, the scripts aim to streamline performance testing while avoiding manual command memorization. The tone is practical and instructional, with code examples and step-by-step setup guidance.",
